        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/introduction"
            style="@style/headingforinfo"
            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
            android:text="Introduction"
            android:background="@color/ilalalight"
            />


        <TextView
            style="@style/textinfo"
            android:text="Birds are the musical instruments, bands, and orchestras of nature, and in many ways are no different from the music we listen to. "
            />

        <TextView
            style="@style/textinfo"
            android:text="If you can identify the ‘’Mama Mia’’ by ABBA, or recognize that the movie you are watching has a score composed by Hans Zimmer, then you can also identify bird calls."
            />

        <TextView
            style="@style/textinfo"
            android:text="Your ability to listen and remember sounds is much more powerful and effective than you might think. The average person might not be able to identify Bon Jovi if he walked into the room, but when ‘’Summer of 69’’ is playing, every person recognizes it and starts singing as if it's their last day on earth."
            />
        <TextView
            style="@style/textinfo"
            android:text="You might struggle at first, but don't worry. Stop, relax, and listen. Don't worry about trying to identify the species right away. Instead, focus on differentiating between the calls of different species. Once you have isolated a particular voice, you can consider, pitch, tempo, quality, mimicry and alarm calls."
            />

