        </LinearLayout>

        <TextView
            style="@style/textinfo"
            android:text="Certain pitch ranges can be described as whistles, with lower-pitched whistles typically being described as ‘‘rich’’ or ‘‘full’’ and higher-pitched whistles as ‘‘thin’’ or ‘’squeaky’’. Similarly, descriptive words like ‘‘relaxed’’ and ‘‘lethargic’’ imply a slower tempo, while a ‘’buzz’’ is like a trill, but at a faster tempo"/>
        <TextView
            style="@style/textinfo"
            android:text="The creative words we use to describe bird songs often convey information about pitch and tempo, which can be helpful for most people in understanding the characteristics of the call. "/>
        <TextView
            style="@style/textinfo"
            android:text="In summary, the term ’quality’ (timbre) refers to how you creatively describe or perceive a bird call in terms of pitch and tempo."/>

        <TextView
